1 WHEREAS, the Medicare Physician Fee Schedule locality structure
2 currently designates all regions of this state under Locality 13, grouping
3 both urban and rural areas into a single reimbursement category despite clear
4 economic and cost-of-practice differences; and
5
6 WHEREAS, the Geographic Practice Cost Indices assigned to this state do
7 not accurately reflect the actual costs incurred by medical practices in its
8 metropolitan areas, placing undue financial strain on healthcare providers,
9 and reducing access to essential medical services for residents; and
10 WHEREAS, Arkansas ranks as the third-worst state in Medicare locality
11 reimbursement, trailing only Mississippi and the "Rest of Missouri"
12 localities, further disadvantaging healthcare providers and limiting patient
13 access to care; and
14
15 WHEREAS, this state's urban centers experience significantly higher
16 commercial lease rates, labor costs, and other operational expenses that
17 necessitate a reevaluation of Medicare Physician Fee Schedule localities to
18 ensure fair Medicare reimbursement and a sustainable healthcare system; and
19
20 WHEREAS, carving out CBSA 22220, which is Fayetteville-Springdale-
21 Rogers, AR, and CBSA 30780, which is Little Rock-North Little Rock-Conway,
22 AR, into separate locality numbers would more accurately reflect the unique
23 economic conditions of these metropolitan areas and align Arkansas with
24 national standards for Medicare locality determination; and
25
26 WHEREAS, failure to correct this misalignment perpetuates inequitable
27 healthcare reimbursement policies that hinder this state's healthcare
28 providers' ability to deliver essential medical services,
29
30 NOW THEREFORE,
31 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL
32 ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS, THE SENATE CONCURRING THEREIN:
33
34 THAT the House of Representatives and the Senate concurring encourages
35 the United States Congress to:
36 (1) Conduct a thorough review of the current Medicare Physician
