2 reimbursement rates align with actual regional cost structures;
3 (2) Examine and reassess the Geographic Practice Cost Indices
4 assigned to this state's localities to guarantee that the Geographic Practice
5 Cost Indices accurately reflect the expenses incurred by healthcare providers
6 in different regions of the state;
7 (3) Carve out CBSA 22220, which is Fayetteville-Springdale-
8 Rogers, AR, and CBSA 30780, which is Little Rock-North Little Rock-Conway,
9 AR, into separate locality numbers to ensure fair reimbursement that reflects
10 the economic realities of these metropolitan areas; and
11 (4) Take swift action to correct these inaccuracies to prevent
12 further financial disadvantages for the healthcare providers of this state
13 and ensure equitable access to medical services for residents.
14
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT upon adoption of this resolution, an
